ide->idle



(1) help()
    - if arg given, string is looked up and a help page printed
    - if no arg, interactive starts
(2) dir()
    - if arg given, returns list of valid attributes for that obj
    - if no arg, returns list of names in the current local scope

EXAMPLE
(1)
help(list) #prompts elaborate list about all methods of the class 'list'

help(str.join) #prompts infos only about the 'join'-method
(2)
dir(list) #returns briefly all methods/attributes of 'list'
